                    <p>To Theo van Gogh. The Hague, on or about Monday, 7 May 1883.</p>
                    <note type="ongoingTopic" n="1">
                        <p>Theo’s love for the ailing Marie <ref target="let300.xml">(300)</ref>
                            </p>
                        </note>
                       <note type="ongoingTopic" n="2">
                        <p>Conflict with Sien’s family <ref target="let338.xml">(338)</ref>
                            </p>
                        </note>
                    </vg:letContents>
                <note type="sourceStatus" xml:id="sourceStatus">
                    <p>Original manuscript</p>
                    </note>
                <note type="location" xml:id="location">
                    <p>Amsterdam, Van Gogh Museum, inv. no. b306 V/1962</p>
                    </note>
                <note type="date" xml:id="date">
                    <p>Van Gogh writes that he has arranged with Van der Weele to go painting together ‘next week’ <ref target="#l-16">(l. 16)</ref>. Assuming that this arrangement was agreed during Van Gogh’s visit to Van der Weele’s studio on Sunday, 6 May (<ref target="let341.xml">see letter 341</ref>), the letter must date from later that day or shortly after it. Because he is fairly desperate and is counting on help even before the second remittance of on or about 10 May <ref target="#l-13">(ll. 13-14)</ref>, we date the letter on or about Monday, 7 May 1883.</p>
                    </note>
                </vg:letDesc>
